### Component

Cast

### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?

- [X] Foundry
- [X] Foundryup

### What version of Foundry are you on?

forge 0.2.0 (85f25c6 2023-11-08T00:33:45.948577000Z)

### What command(s) is the bug in?

cast interface

### Operating System

macOS (Intel)

### Describe the bug

The interface generated by `cast` does not include the `payable` modifier on address params.

This is non-critical since values can always be casted, but it makes integrations more difficult when using the generated interface and expecting a payable return param (or a `address payable[] memory`). 

Example contract:
```solidity
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.18;

contract Payable {
  function getPayable() external view returns (address payable) {
    return payable(address(this));
  }

  function setPayable(address payable test) external pure {
    test;
  }
}
```

`cast interface <(forge inspect Payable abi)` outputs:
```solidity
pragma solidity ^0.8.10;

interface Interface {
    function getPayable() external view returns (address);
    function setPayable(address test) external pure;
}
```

Expected:
```solidity
pragma solidity ^0.8.10;

interface Interface {
    function getPayable() external view returns (address payable);
    function setPayable(address payable test) external pure;
}
```
